        contraction increases the enclosed DM halo mass by factors of
        roughly 1.3, 2, and 4 at radial distances of 20, 8, and 1 kpc,
        respectively compared to an uncontracted halo. Ignoring this
        contraction results in systematic biases in the inferred halo
