        infers that the DM density at the Solar position is ρ<sub>⊙</sub><sup>DM</sup>=8.8<sub>-0.5</sub><sup>+0.5</sup> ×
        10<sup>-3</sup> M<sub>⊙</sub> pc<sup>-3</sup> ≡
        0.33<sub>-0.02</sub><sup>+0.02</sup> GeV cm<sup>-3</sup>. The rotation
        curve data can also be fitted with an uncontracted NFW halo
